00:56:57,540 --> 00:56:58,416
That's all practical.

1202
00:56:58,499 --> 00:57:00,561
- End up with moments like that.
- Some flares.

1203
00:57:00,585 --> 00:57:02,795
- Yeah.
- All that's real, practical.

1204
00:57:02,878 --> 00:57:05,673
And this is
in Stone Mountain in Atlanta.

1205
00:57:05,756 --> 00:57:07,633
Real train tracks.
We didn't pay for those.

1206
00:57:08,467 --> 00:57:10,303
No, we built those from scratch.

1207
00:57:11,137 --> 00:57:13,097
Well, we built the EDO from scratch.

1208
00:57:13,306 --> 00:57:15,766
And then we had a lot
of conversations about,

1209
00:57:15,850 --> 00:57:17,852
"How do we make this EDO look...

1210
00:57:18,686 --> 00:57:20,896
recognizable, but not too obvious?"

1211
00:57:20,980 --> 00:57:23,166
And there was a conversation
about how many rocks should go in the E.

1212
00:57:23,190 --> 00:57:25,318
You came over to me
looking really worried,

1213
00:57:25,401 --> 00:57:27,838
and I know that when you come over
looking really worried you said,

1214
00:57:27,862 --> 00:57:29,447
"Jen, the E."

1215
00:57:29,697 --> 00:57:31,907
So, we were moving
the rocks around on the E.

1216
00:57:31,991 --> 00:57:34,952
It was so perfect, that it made
it seem like, "How could you miss"

1217
00:57:35,036 --> 00:57:37,371
this clue to the secret camp?
Everyone would be there."

1218
00:57:37,747 --> 00:57:39,040
Oh, dear.

1219
00:57:39,165 --> 00:57:40,726
<i>- Hey, we're not armed.
- Save it, asshole.</i>

1220
00:57:40,750 --> 00:57:41,626
<i>Hold on.</i>

